headline: Thermo Fisher beats quarterly estimates on resilient demand for its tools and services
summary: Shares of the medical equipment maker were up 2.5% in premarket trading.  The company joins peers such as Danaher in beating quarterly profit estimates, citing strong demand from the industry for tools and services used to make vaccines and therapies.  Danaher said on Tuesday it is seeing a robust number of clinical trials and therapies under development, with steady demand from its pharmaceutical clients.
